How to use
==========

Sun Java Runtime Environment (JRE) is required for train-graph
program. Currently, train-graph only works with Sun JRE. 

You can obtain the installation package for Sun JRE at
http://www.java.com/en/download/manual.jsp

For Linux user, you can start the train-graph program by the following
command:
$ java -jar ETRC.jar

For Windows user, simply double click on the ETRC.jar file to run the
program.

train-graph will use the system locale to show it's user
interface. Currently only English and Simplified Chinese is
supported. You are more than welcome to contribute on the UI
translation and wording. Please contact with us for translation
related work.


How to contact
==============

If you have any suggestion or questions, please feel free to submit Issue
on train-graph Google Code page: 

http://code.google.com/p/train-graph/issues/list

You can also send email to lifanxi <AT> freemindworld.com for any issues. 


